HEADWORD: Ganocephala
<hw>Gan`o*ceph"a*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ brightness + <?/ head.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A group of fossil amphibians allied to the
labyrinthodonts, having the head defended by bony, sculptured plates, as
in some ganoid fishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

